Text.Value: You claim knowledge beyond us?
I expected no visitors, faithful or otherwise. Why have you come?
Walk well within Cr√®che Y'llek, ra'stil.
Tsk'va... It speaks truth. The inquisitor will be most pleased.

Text.Value: Do not cite protocol to me, shka'keth.
Try me. Htak'a!
At least the weapon is here. Inquisitor W'wargaz will be pleased.
Is that so? His efficiency is to be commended then, as is yours.

EditorData.NodeContext: Excited, almost forgetting the stuffy gith decorum

Text.Value: Silence! I will tear her name from your impure tongue.
Produce the artefact as evidence.
Report to the infirmary at once. Step carefully, istik, Cr√®che Y'llek watches you.
Sentries, to arms! Istik. State your purpose. Quickly.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [MainGith] steps forward to confront PLYR. Check if V.O anim can be used. If not use Custom or CINE. <LoganP>
EditorData.NodeContext: 'istik' pronounced iss-tick - "quickly" said as a threat

Text.Value: Attack.
Your insolent species knows nothing of authority, k'chakhi. Let me teach you.
Very well. Perhaps Inquisitor W'wargaz could use the aid of an adventurer.
I have the weapon Voss was looking for, that your cr√®che wanted found.
Attack.
Perhaps the news you bring will change Inquisitor W'wargaz's mind.
The ghustil has been taking an... Unprecedented interest in the ghaik tadpoles of late.

EditorData.NodeContext: almost disgusted? these guards aren't on board with the rumours they've heard about their doctor

Text.Value: I was told to bring the weapon to the highest authority possible. That doesn't look like you.
Kith'rak Voss instructed me to bring a weapon to our kin. I have found it.
Report to the captain. She will take you to the Inquisitor.
I hunt monsters. Either that's you, or it's the mind flayers - your choice.
Let me pass. Fighting me will end badly for you.
You could turn at any moment. I will not let a ghaik abomination endanger my kin.
I've been infected for a while. Your doctors could study me.
My 'purpose' is to reap death upon you.
Attack.
You could turn at any moment. I will protect my kin. Hta'zith!
I'm an unmatched killer. You want me as your ally.
Shkath zai. We were not expecting visitors, kin. What brings you here?
I SPEAK AS AN AVATAR OF QUEEN VLAAKITH. YOU WILL LET ME PASS, VIN'IISK.
I was infected by an illithid, and was told to seek a githyanki cr√®che.
I will report to your kith'rak as protocol dictates. Do not forget yourself.
A ghaik thrall is something to eradicate, not reason with.
If you are lying, it'll be a painful death. The Inquisitor is deeper in the cr√®che.
Kith'rak Voss was searching for a weapon. I have it with me.
You've talked to one of our queen's silver knights, and hold the lost weapon? Prove it, istik.
Faithful gish, Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai.

EditorData.NodeContext: VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI. For the honour of Vlaakith.

Text.Value: Leave.
Stand aside, or crumble in combat.
...An avatar? Of the undying regent herself? I beg your mercy, jhe'stil.

EditorData.NodeContext: ''zhe-STILL. (/ í/ sound on first consonant, like the "s" in "usual".)'' meaning ''superior one''

Text.Value: Inquisitor W'wargaz will be honoured to meet you. Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith.

EditorData.NodeContext: "cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith" meaning "Vlaakith's will above all"

Text.Value: Allow Lae'zel to answer.
You are infected?
The ceremorphosis is delayed. Your cr√®che's doctors would find me useful to study.
If that is so, you succeed where others have failed.
Chk... It wouldn't be the strangest study she's done.
Ra'stil, listen. I am infected by ghaik, your mandate is to aid me.
Produce this weapon and you may pass.
You may proceed.
Stand down, gish. Is it not Vlaakith's command to welcome her faithful?
You githyanki hate illithid. I have proof that they're invading. We need your help.
I'm on your side! Captain Voss sent me to find an item for you.
I found the weapon you seek. Want to explain to Voss why you killed me?
Ra'stil... You bring great honour on Cr√®che Y'llek this day. The Inquisitor will be pleased.

Text.Value: You are infected. A source of plague. Nothing more.
Allow Lae'zel to answer.
What are you doing?!
What are you doing?!
Kith'rak Voss entrusted me with finding a weapon. I have done so, you will let me pass.
We are aware, and it is dire. But of late we've been distracted.
Arrogant, for such a limited species.
We seek the zaith'isk. Show me the way.
Report to the infirmary at once. And step carefully. Cr√®che Y'llek watches you.
Halt. We were not expecting visitors, kin. What brings you here?
I dare you to try. Otherwise, step aside, shka'keth.
I'm no thrall. I came here freely, didn't I?
Fine. Report to the infirmary. Quickly.
Attack.
Forgive me, ra'stil. Our nerves are somewhat heightened with the Inquisition's presence.

EditorData.NodeContext: "cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith" meaning "Vlaakith's will above all"

Text.Value: Try to recall and invoke the ancient githyanki war rites of parley.
Chk. Fine - let the ghustil carry out your fate.
Your corpse would be just as useful, ghaik filth.
The faithful may be purified. This is Vlaakith's protocol!
*The artefact stirs within your pocket - suddenly within your reach, but reluctant to be known to the githyanki.*
*The sentry considers you for a moment, assessing the risk you pose.*
Chk. The Inquisitor better not hear of this. Report to the infirmary.
Go, seek Inquisitor W'wargaz within. Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith.
Seek the inquisitor within. Step lightly, ra'stil - he's not known for his lenience.
Seek the Inquisitor within. Step lightly, istik - he's not known for his lenience.
There is a ghaik scourge in these lands. I need this cr√®che's help.

Synopsis: The guards can be convinced to let you in if you are Gith-looking, produce the box, or persuade them you have a reason to be at the creche.
